07722,-0.02239240,0.04587914,0.02969753,-0.02620279,0.01251661,0.00740461,-0.01362734,-0.00451589,-0.02546435,0.03202422,0.02335708,0.04150349,-0.05489310,0.00590710,0.01258729,0.02222439,-0.03402395,-0.08795340,0.02223748,0.03395830,0.04104683,0.08961564,-0.03137580,-0.04977882,-0.07088238,0.02755369,0.02195407,-0.06602407,-0.09009676,-0.01112093,0.01994560,0.01272818,0.02613438,0.01556341,-0.00311262,-0.03863287,0.01931728,0.04740891,-0.05547614,0.07543698,-0.06596195,-0.03416342]',E'Dial retries and backoff\n\nConnection establishment can be retried by the connection pool when dialing fails.\n\n- **`DialerRetries`**: maximum number of dial attempts (default: 5).\n- **`DialerRetryTimeout`**: default delay between attempts when no custom backoff is provided (default: 100ms).\n- **`DialerRetryBackoff`**: optional function hook to control the delay between attempts.\n\nExample:\n\n```go\nrdb := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n	Addr: "localhost:6379",\n\n	DialerRetries:      5,\n	DialerRetryTimeout: 100 * time.Millisecond, // used when DialerRetryBackoff is nil\n\n	// Optional: exponential backoff with jitter and a cap.\n	DialerRetryBackoff: redis.DialRetryBackoffExponential(100*time.Millisecond, 2*time.Second),\n})\ndefer rdb.Close()\n```','{"source": "redis", "version": "7", "language": "go", "title": "Redis client for Go", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/redis/go-redis/blob/master/README.md", "topics": "redis,go,cache,README", "categories": "database,cache,go"}');
